stimulus:
The Illusion Game

In this reaction-time game, you will need to be as fast as possible and make correct responses by resisting different visual illusions.

We will show you examples of each illusion before each block.

Remember, your goal is to be as fast and accurate as possible. Good luck!

Part 1

In this part, two red circles will appear side by side on the screen.

Your task is to select which red circle is bigger in size as fast as you can, without making errors.

Don't get distracted by the black outlines around the red circles!

Press the left or the right arrow to indicate where is the biggest red circle.

In this example, the correct answer is the left arrow.

Are you ready? Press ENTER to start

Your score for this illusion is

4246

You performed better than 65.43% of the population.

Can you do better in the next illusion?

In this part, two red circles will appear side by side on the screen.

Your task is to select which red circle is bigger in size as fast as you can, without making errors.

Don't get distracted by the surrounding black circles around the red circles!

Press the left or the right arrow to indicate where is the biggest red circle.

In this example, the correct answer is the left arrow.

Are you ready? Press ENTER to start

Part 3

In this part, two horizontal red lines will appear above and below on the screen.

Your task is to select which line is longer in size as fast as you can, without making errors.

Don't get distracted by the surrounding black arrows at the end of the red lines!

Press the UP or the DOWN arrow to indicate where is the longest red line.

In this example, the correct answer is the UP arrow.
